From the beat to the style to the lyrics, Simi’s flawless musical act seams through. In her latest release “Small Ting”, she shows us her production prowess one more time and it is evident that she is a fast-learning student (having taken courses in production.) Speaking about the self-produced song, Simi wrote on Instagram, “This is the actual first beat I’ve made. It was a project for class. I wanted it to mean something, and so I wrote/recorded a song on it.” She harpers on the small things (ting) that people in our society make a huge deal out of. Check out Simi, the student’s song: 